                    "type": "sight",
                    "title": "Tuscany Wine Tour, Siena and San Gimignano - Small Group Tour",
                    "description": "{\"sightseeing_id\":186,\"result_index\":20,\"sightseeing_name\":\"Tuscany Wine Tour, Siena and San Gimignano - Small Group Tour\",\"sightseeing_code\":\"E-E10-A0MPNO0053\",\"city_id\":134622,\"tour_summary\":null,\"condition_text\":\"E-voucher. Show the voucher on your mobile device to enjoy the activity.\",\"guidelines\":null,\"additional_information\":\"Please make sure you answer all the mandatory questions during the booking process.\",\"total_duration\":\"1 DAYS\",\"from_date\":\"2024-09-04 00:00:00\",\"tour_desc\":\"Enjoy a full-day journey from Rome, through the Chianti hills, to visit the cities of San Gimignano and Siena.<br />\\n<br />\\n<strong>Highlights</strong><br />\\n• Visit the Tuscan towns of San Gimignano and Siena from Rome<br />\\n• Travel in a small group tour max 6 people<br />\\n• Enjoy the experience of living a day in Tuscany<br />\\n•Taste Tuscan food and wine at local winery<br />\\n<br />\\nSan Gimignano, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, is known as “The City of the Hundred Towers” and it still maintains its original features and timeless charm. Furthermore, the name 'San Gimignano' is linked to one of the most historical Tuscan wines:” La Vernaccia di San Gimignano”. Arriving in San Gimignano you will explore its charming medieval streets, visit the old center of this wonderful city where the famous Chianti wine is produced. Stop for a wine tasting and local products in a beautiful wine cellar: 10 different types of wine and oil, then visit the estate and learn about the processing of the grapes. Lunch at the restaurant of the estate.<br />\\n<br />\\nThen continue to Siena, a beautiful medieval city in Italy. You will visit the heart of Siena and the central square known as “Piazza del Campo”, known worldwide for the famous “Palio”, a horse race twice around the square in a medieval-style every summer. Siena is famous not only for its wine but also for its sweets: the “Panpepato”, “Panforte”, “Ricciarelli”. Stop for a good Italian coffee and taste a typical sweet of Siena. Departure for Rome at 5pm.<br/><br/><strong>Inclusions: </strong>FOODINCL,Tasting of local products<br>OTHERINCL,Tour escort<br>DRINKSINCL,Wine tasting<br>TRANSPORTINCL,Air-conditioned transportation<br>TRANSPORTINCL,Hotel pick-up and drop-off for selected hotels<br><br/><br/><strong>Exclusions: </strong>OTHERNOT,Any additional expenses which are not included or detailed in the programme.<br>DRINKSNOT,Additional drinks<br>\",\"plan\":[{\"code\":\"974767171#GENERAL|06:30\",\"languages\":\"ENG\",\"special_text\":\"Tour english 06:30|ENG\",\"tour_details\":null,\"currency_code\":\"INR\",\"offered_price\":20096.4,\"published_price\":20096.4,\"agent_commission\":0,\"cancellation_fee\":\"100.00%\",\"last_cancellation_date\":\"2024-08-29 23:59:59.000000\"}],\"city_name\":\"Rome\",\"country_code\":\"IT\",\"sight_types\":[\"activities\"],\"images\":[{\"image_url\":\"https://media.activitiesbank.com/51420/ENG/B/20181109_134858.jpg\"}],\"notes\":\"The activity duration is inferred from the provided information. The activity is considered kid-friendly due to its educational and entertainment value. The physical intensity is inferred to be low as the activity primarily involves visiting cultural and historical sites. The best time of day is inferred from the available schedule.\",\"api_used\":\"fireworks_mixtral_22b\",\"best_for\":[\"couples\",\"families\",\"groups\",\"history buffs\",\"art enthusiasts\",\"food connoisseurs\"],\"category\":[\"cultural\",\"historical\",\"culinary\",\"scenic\",\"rural experience\"],\"kid_friendly\":true,\"transit_type\":null,\"drop_provided\":true,\"food_provided\":true,\"available_times\":[\"06:30\"],\"pickup_provided\":true,\"best_time_of_day\":\"morning\",\"duration_minutes\":720,\"relaxation_level\":4,\"physical_intensity\":2,\"is_transit_activity\":false,\"unique_experience_rating\":5}",
